I am a developer in training .Build me a landing page of an online take-away Nigeria meal restaurant with the name MamaPutOnline. MamaPutOnline sells different types of cooked soups - egusi, ewedu, ora, edikaikong, okazi, ogbono and okro It also sells jollof rice, fried rice, porridge yam, porridge beans, fried plantain, abacha, nkwobi, fried chicken, kpomo , roosted plantain etc. 
Menu Section Let the landing page have a - MamaPutOnline logo on the top left hand corner - Menu bar in dark red with sub titles like Products, Services, Customer Service, Contact Us - A search window on the very top right hand corner. Hero Section Below the menu bar section, let there be a hero section with a Call-To-Action button The hero section should occupy at least 30% of the vertical length of the page and 100% of the breathe of the page. A hero section should be vertically partitioned into two One side of the hero section should display the picture of a steaming, deliciously-cooked Nigerian dish / soup (with the right aspect ratio and with the right pixelization) The other side of the hero section should have boldly-written words in large print, lettering inviting people to not miss the opportunity to buy from your online store ****** Main Section Have a side panel on the left of the main section with items listed there and connecting users to the main section / product cards Have at least three rows on the landing page...on the right side of the side panel...with each row have 5 product cards The product cards should identify the product boldly, the quantity and the price in Naira and add a hover effect in the price text and background color changes to a different color from its original color. 
 Let the landing page also have a footer that has all the social media links ******** Build your page using HTML, CSS and / or Tailwind CSS and also use the IDE visual studio code ******* Make the site fully responsive for mobile users, since many take-away orders will come from smartphones. Ensure that the Menu and Footer are sticky